# Responsive Design Rules — StyleUp ERP Dashboard

## Breakpoints (Tailwind default, do not override)

- sm: 640px
- md: 768px
- lg: 1024px
- xl: 1280px
- 2xl: 1536px

## Core principles

- Mobile-first. Write base styles for mobile, layer up with sm:/md:/lg:/xl:.
- All JavaScript breakpoint checks must use `useResponsive` from `@/shared/hooks/use-responsive`. Never call `matchMedia`, `window.innerWidth`, or attach resize listeners in components.
- Never use fixed pixel widths on containers, cards, or charts. Use %, fr, or max-w-* with w-full.
- Never hardcode breakpoint values inline (no `@media (min-width: 810px)`). Only use Tailwind breakpoint prefixes.
- All spacing must come from the shared spacing scale (gap-2, gap-4, gap-6, p-4, p-6). No arbitrary values like p-[13px].
- All new components must be checked at sm, md, lg, xl before being marked done.

## Layout rules

- Grids: use the shared `ResponsiveGrid` component or `grid.*` tokens from `src/theme/responsive.ts` instead of redefining grid-cols-* per component.
- Two-column or multi-column sections must collapse to single column below lg (charts) or per theme preset.
- Sidebars/filters that are fixed on desktop must become drawer/sheet/accordion on mobile — never horizontally compress.
- Sticky headers/toolbars must include safe z-index from theme (`zIndex.stickyHeader`) and must not overlap content on scroll at any breakpoint.

## Cards (KPI, activity, etc.)

- Use shared `Card` and `KpiCard` components only. No one-off card markup.
- Text inside cards truncates with `truncate` + Tooltip via `TruncatedText` — never wraps and breaks card height.
- Icon and font sizes step down at sm using theme `typography.*` tokens, not manual overrides.

## Charts

- All charts must be wrapped in shadcn `ChartContainer` (recharts ResponsiveContainer inside) — no fixed width/height props on containers.
- Provide mobile behavior via the shared `useChartResponsive` hook and `chart.mobileConfig` from theme.
- Multi-series charts must have a simplified mobile variant, not just a shrunk version of desktop.

## Tables / lists

- Tables convert to card/list layout below md using the shared `ResponsiveTable` component when available.
- No native horizontal-scroll tables unless explicitly approved — check with shared component first.

## Loading states

- Skeletons must match the responsive dimensions of the final content at each breakpoint. No fixed-size skeletons that cause layout shift when real content loads.

## Enforcement

- Before marking any dashboard task complete, verify: no fixed px widths added, no inline media queries, no ad-hoc spacing values, all breakpoint prefixes match the scale above.
- If a new responsive pattern is needed that isn't covered here, add it to `src/theme/responsive.ts` first, then use it — don't solve it locally in the component.
